              <li>Better team collaboration</li>
              <li>Consistent user experience</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <h2 class="h3 mt-5 mb-3">Progressive Web Applications (PWAs)</h2>
          <p>Progressive Web Applications continue to gain momentum as they bridge the gap between web and native mobile applications. PWAs offer app-like experiences while maintaining the reach and accessibility of web applications.</p>

          <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1563986768609-322da13575f3?w=600&h=300&fit=crop&crop=center" class="img-fluid rounded my-4" alt="Mobile development" style="width: 100%; height: 300px; object-fit: cover;">

          <h2 class="h3 mt-5 mb-3">Server-Side Rendering (SSR) and Static Site Generation</h2>
          <p>The balance between client-side and server-side rendering has become a crucial consideration for modern web applications. Technologies like Next.js, Nuxt.js, and Gatsby have made it easier to implement hybrid approaches that optimize for both performance and SEO.</p>

          <blockquote class="blockquote border-start border-primary border-4 ps-4 py-3 my-4 bg-light">
